<br>
On the whole 'Hail Friend' thing... it's called being polite. You're asking for a favour and most of us act nice when we want something (regardless of whether or not we are polite normally). It's only fair really, you are imposing on someone, the least you can do is make it as pleasant as possible for them (in my case, it usually means I take a bath, to make myself less odiferous).<br>
<br>
I quite often say other things as well, such as hi, hey, sup?, whatever... the point is, to get upset about the mode of address is just silly. There is no difference whatsoever. Whereas saying 'Yo Rez Bitch, get yo ass here' (Or something to that effect) is gonna be taken the wrong way 90% of the time, especially when you've never met the person before.  Besides, even if I don't ever meet you again, it doesn't mean I won't remember the fact that you helped me out.<br>
<br>
As far as the rest of it goes, it's all spot on. It's also been said before, so I see no reason to comment on it. Sorry to rant a bit (bah what am I saying? It's a rant board!), but really... getting upset over someone starting a res request with 'Hail Friend' is just ridiculous. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13112">Mordi Tashkarii</a><br>Warlord<BR>
